{{Quote|Of course. I haven't heard of Grand Admiral Thrawn, either. Certainly not in connection with the ''Chimaera''. Or with some intriguing information raids on several systems in the Paonnid/Obroa-skai region, either.|Talon Karrde|<ref name="HttE">''[[Heir to the Empire]]''</ref>}}
The '''Paonnid''' were a [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Species/Legends|species]] from the [[Paonid system/Legends|Paonid system]]. In [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]], while wandering on a marketplace on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Bimmisaari/Legends|Bimmisaari]], the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] hero [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] spotted a being who looked like a Paonnid among the crowd.<ref name="HttE" />

They produced [[Paonidd extrassa art|extrassa art]] similar to the [[Saffa paintings]] and the pre-Empire [[Vaathkree (species)|Vaathkree]] [[Flatsculp/Legends|flatsculp]].<ref name="HttE" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Paonnid, the Paonid system and the Paonidd extrassa art were first mentioned in the novel ''[[Heir to the Empire]]'', which used instinctively the spellings Paonnid and Paonidd.<ref name="HttE" /> Likely for simplification, later sources only used the spelling Paonid.<ref name="HttES">''[[Heir to the Empire Sourcebook]]''</ref><ref name="TCSWE">{{CSWECite|II||Obroa-skai}}</ref><ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>

